                  <summary>An order by a certain Appianus to a brickmaker to supply a designated person with one thousand bricks. The order was written for Appianus by his secretary or agent who has the uncommon name, Phasganius, a name which has occured only once in all Greek Literature. Phasganius sent his own son&lt; Argaios, to get the bricks.</summary>
